Trivia

    "For great science" references the internet meme "For great justice", which originated from the Engrish translation of the game Zero Wing.
    "Back, you dirty ape, back!" references Planet of the Apes.
    "Raise your what?" references ヽ༼ຈل͜ຈ༽ﾉ raise your dongers by Michael 'Imaqtpie' Santana from Team Dignitas.
    "The probability of your continued existence is rapidly approaching zero" was used in Rumble's Rumble's League Judgement.
    "Not enough variables... hmm... not nearly enough variables" references Mordin Solus from Mass Effect 2 ("Too many variables")
    "42... there's just something about that number" and "Aha, 42, I knew it! Now--- er, what was the question again?" reference The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy.
        A side-by-side comparison can be seen here.
    In Brazilian localization Heimerdinger has a joke referencing El Chavo del Ocho.
    "I prefer a battle of wits, but you're unarmed!" references William Shakespeare ("I would challenge you to a battle of wits, but I see you are unarmed!")
    Dragon Trainer Heimerdinger's line "AVOID SWOOPING, SWOOPING IS BAD." is a reference to one of Alistar's witty one-liners from Dragon Age Origins.


